items.details: Red Hat has identified that your cluster is no longer owned by a user with an enabled Red Hat account. This will impact the cluster's ability to upgrade to future versions. Please raise a support case with Red Hat to nominate a new owner for the cluster in https://cloud.redhat.com/openshift/
Red Hat has identified that your cluster is running a configuration that is inhibiting normal operation. Please see the service log for more details, or contact Red Hat support for more information.

Red Hat has identified that the cloud provider account hosting your cluster is running a configuration that is inhibiting normal operation. Please see the service log for more details, or contact Red Hat support for more information.
